### ======================================================================
### LIBRARIAN API TESTS - Foco em EmployeeID e CRUD completo
### ======================================================================

### PASSO 0: Limpar todos os Bibliotecários (CUIDADO!)
DELETE http://localhost:3000/librarians

### ---
### PASSO 1: Listar todos os Bibliotecários (deve estar vazio)
GET http://localhost:3000/librarians
Accept: application/json

### ======================================================================
### PASSO 2: CRIAR BIBLIOTECÁRIOS com EmployeeIDs conhecidos
### ======================================================================

### Criar Bibliotecário 1: "Ana Supervisora" com EmployeeID {{employee_id_ana}}
POST http://localhost:3000/librarians
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ana Supervisora",
  "email": "admin@bibliotech.com",
  "employeeId": "SUP001", 
  "password": "superSenhaAna123",
  "role": "Manager"
}

### ---
### Criar Bibliotecário 2: "Bruno Atendente" com EmployeeID {{employee_id_bruno}}
POST http://localhost:3000/librarians
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bruno Atendente",
  "email": "bruno.atende@bibliotech.com",
  "employeeId": "ATD007",
  "password": "atendenteSeguro789",
  "role": "Staff" 
}


### ======================================================================
### PASSO 3: LISTAR TODOS OS BIBLIOTECÁRIOS
### ======================================================================

GET http://localhost:3000/librarians
Accept: application/json
# Esperado: Lista com Ana e Bruno, sem passwordHash


### ======================================================================
### PASSO 4: OPERAÇÕES POR EMPLOYEE_ID
### ======================================================================

### Buscar "Ana Supervisora" PELO EMPLOYEE_ID {{employee_id_ana}}
GET http://localhost:3000/librarians/employee/SUP001
Accept: application/json

### ---
### Atualizar "Bruno Atendente" (employeeId {{employee_id_bruno}}) PELO EMPLOYEE_ID
PUT http://localhost:3000/librarians/employee/ATD007
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "bruno.promovido@bibliotech.com",
  "role": "Admin"
}

### ---
### Verificar a atualização do Bruno (buscando pelo employeeId {{employee_id_bruno}})
GET http://localhost:3000/librarians/employee/ATD007
Accept: application/json

### ---
### Deletar "Ana Supervisora" (employeeId {{employee_id_ana}}) PELO EMPLOYEE_ID
DELETE http://localhost:3000/librarians/employee/SUP001

### ---
### Tentar buscar "Ana Supervisora" pelo employeeId {{employee_id_ana}} (deve dar 404)
GET http://localhost:3000/librarians/employee/SUP001
Accept: application/json

### ---
### Listar todos os Bibliotecários (só deve ter "Bruno Atendente" atualizado agora)
GET http://localhost:3000/librarians
Accept: application/json
